Two men due to appear before Mthatha Magistrate Court facing charges of possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. This comes after SAPS members stopped and searched a silver grey Mazda 323 with two occupants near Mthatha Police Station on the R61 road on Sunday. During the search, a police 9mm Norinco Pistol with two rounds of ammunition and a 9mm Parabellum Pistol with six rounds of ammunition were discovered. It was found that both firearms were linked to a 2006 Coffee Bay case and the Parabellum was positively linked to a 2017 Peddie case. -TNA Reporter 